definition.value: A westward-flowing stream in Mendocino County, California which empties into the Pacific Ocean in Van Damme State Park near the town of Little River, California.

A river in Mendocino County, California. The river's headwaters are thirty miles inland from the Pacific Ocean in the Mendocino Range, part of the California Coast Range. The headwater area of the river is fed by Montgomery Creek as it flows through the upland riparian habitat and virgin redwoods of Montgomery Woods State Reserve. From there, the river flows roughly west through Jackson State Demonstration Forest. The lower portions of the river pass through Mendocino Woodlands State Park and the Big River Unit of Mendocino Headlands State Park before reaching the mouth of the river at the Pacific Ocean just south of the town of Mendocino.

A river on the north coast of California in Mendocino County. The river's headwaters are in the steep Mendocino Range, but downstream the river flows through gently sloping marine terraces before draining into the Pacific Ocean.

A river in upper Northern California. It flows for 150 km in a roughly northwest direction through Trinity County and then Humboldt County, draining a 1290 km2 watershed into the Pacific Ocean near Arcata-Eureka Airport in McKinleyville. The upper half of the river is inside the Six Rivers National Forest.
A river.

A river in Humboldt County, California. The river's headwaters are in the Coast Range at about 5,000 feet and it flows roughly northwest until it empties into the Pacific Ocean near the small town of Orick.

A river on the Pacific coast of northern California in the United States. It is formed by the confluence of its Middle and North forks in Del Norte County, in the extreme northwest corner of California, near the community of Gasquet.

A major river in southern Oregon and northern California in the United States. It begins at the outlet of Upper Klamath Lake. From Lake Ewauna, the Klamath River flows generally southwest, passing the now-drained bed of the once-vast Lower Klamath Lake before descending into the southern Cascade Range below Keno, Oregon. Once through the Oregon Cascades, the river continues into northern California, passing through the Klamath Mountains and along the southern side of the Siskiyou Mountains. It enters the Pacific at Klamath in southwestern Del Norte County, approximately 32 km south of Crescent City.
A westward-flowing stream in the California counties of Sonoma and Marin, which flows into the Estero Americano.

An approximately nine-mile-long waterway in southwestern Los Angeles County, California, that drains the Los Angeles basin, from the Santa Monica Mountains on the north, the Harbor Freeway (110) on the east, and the Baldwin Hills on the south. It flows through Culver City and the Del Rey district before discharging to Santa Monica Bay between the Marina del Rey and Playa del Rey districts.
A dry wash which carries flashfloods from Tehachapi, California, USA into the Mojave desert during infrequent rains.
An ephemeral river.
A river on the northern coast of California, in southern Mendocino County. The river empties into the Pacific Ocean just north of Point Arena.

A river in Mono County, California, United States. It begins its course as Mammoth Creek, originating in lakes above the town of Mammoth Lakes, California, just south of Mammoth Mountain. The stream water is derived primarily from melting snow as it leaves Twin Lakes. It flows into Long Valley Caldera.

A river on the eastern Oregon high desert which drains a relatively arid basin, the southern portion of Harney Basin, from roughly 30 to 130 km south-southeast of Burns including Malheur National Wildlife Refuge. It arises as an intermittent stream on the lower slopes west of Steens Mountain. It empties into Malheur Lake.

A river in eastern Oregon. It drains a significant amount of the northern Harney Basin. The headwaters are near the southern edge of the Blue Mountains peak named Strawberry Mountain which is approximately 10 miles southeast of John Day, Oregon and about 45 miles NNE of Burns. Significant tributaries of this arid area include Bear Creek and Emigrant Creek. The river runs generally southward and passes near Seneca, Oregon and Burns, Oregon. A few miles southeast of Burns, the river splits into two rivers, East Fork Silvies River and West Fork Silvies River. Both terminate at Malheur Lake about 25 miles southeast of Burns.

A river in coastal San Luis Obispo County that discharges to Morro Bay. Los Osos Creek rises in the Clark Valley on the slopes of the Irish Hills. After flowing through Clark Valley, Los Osos Creek flows into Los Osos Valley.
A coastal river in San Luis Obispo County, California, USA. This watercourse discharges to the Pacific Ocean at the city of Morro Bay.
A river in California running from Grant Lake to Mono Lake. It marks the end of the watercourse that starts at June Lake and continues through the June Lake Loop.
A river in the northern California counties of Marin and Sonoma which empties into Bodega Bay.
A river that runs through Big Basin Redwoods State Park in Santa Cruz County, California. It empties into the Pacific Ocean at Waddell Beach.

A year-round river in southern Marin County, California, USA. It drains the south-eastern slopes of Mount Tamalpais and much of the area in and around the town of Mill Valley; this stream discharges to Richardson Bay.
A river in Marin County, California, United States. It descends the western slope of the Bolinas Ridge and drains into Bolinas Lagoon.
A coastal river in Marin County, California, United States. It descends the western slope of Bolinas Ridge and drains into Bolinas Lagoon.
A river in eastern Marin County, California, United States. It originates on Burdell Mountain above the city of Novato, California and empties into San Pablo Bay south of Petaluma Point.
A south-flowing river in western Marin County, California, United States which empties into Bolinas Lagoon.
A river in Marin County, California. It drains a 18 km2 watershed which includes the Muir Woods National Monument, and reaches the Pacific Ocean north of the Golden Gate at Muir Beach.

A river in Marin County, California, USA that discharges to San Rafael Bay, a small embayment of the San Francisco Bay. The mouth of San Rafael Creek is a channelized estuary through an industrial area.

A northwest-flowing river in western Marin County, California, United States. It originates at the confluence of Salmon Creek and Arroyo Sausal and empties into Tomales Bay south of Dillon Beach, California.
A river in Presidio of San Francisco in San Francisco, California.
A river in San Francisco, California that has been largely culverted. The only remaining portion above ground is in the Mission Creek Channel that drains into China Basin.
A river in San Francisco, California. It is one of the last remaining free flowing, unculverted creeks in San Francisco. It runs from the foothills of the Presidio to the Pacific Ocean.
A river in San Francisco, California.
A small river in San Francisco, California.
A river in San Francisco, California located in The Presidio.
A river.
A small river in Santa Cruz County, California, United States, in the southern San Francisco Bay Area.
A river in western Sonoma County, California that springs from coastal hills west of the town of Occidental and empties into the Pacific Ocean north of Bodega Head.
